25
00:02:07,430 --> 00:02:09,510
(Previously)
Who did this to you?

26
00:02:09,980 --> 00:02:10,770
Who?

27
00:02:10,960 --> 00:02:14,090
The one who killed your father
was a merman.

28
00:02:14,520 --> 00:02:16,890
There's something you should know…

29
00:02:17,080 --> 00:02:18,970
about what happened 20 years ago.

30
00:02:19,550 --> 00:02:21,240
If I don't see Ping tonight…

31
00:02:21,240 --> 00:02:22,760
I'll never see him again.

32
00:02:22,890 --> 00:02:23,810
Is Ping a merman?

33
00:02:24,610 --> 00:02:25,790
I'm sorry, Ping.

34
00:02:28,200 --> 00:02:29,660
That you're not a replacement for anyone.

35
00:02:30,910 --> 00:02:31,680
But because…

36
00:02:32,240 --> 00:02:33,320
I really do love you.

37
00:02:34,350 --> 00:02:35,740
You're going to kill Nawa.

38
00:02:36,380 --> 00:02:37,900
When he saw what we really are,

39
00:02:38,570 --> 00:02:39,400
he was terrified.

40
00:02:39,930 --> 00:02:41,980
He looked at us like we were monsters.

41
00:02:43,050 --> 00:02:44,950
So from now on, I'll live with you.

42
00:02:45,670 --> 00:02:46,980
After everything,

43
00:02:47,740 --> 00:02:49,860
Nawa's decided he won't hide
his identity anymore.

44
00:02:51,250 --> 00:02:53,930
And you...
But from now on, let's live separately.

45
00:02:54,450 --> 00:02:55,570
Stay out of Nawa's life.

46
00:02:56,390 --> 00:02:57,770
If you don't, I'll collide into you.

47
00:02:58,430 --> 00:02:59,940
It's been a few days now.

48
00:03:00,480 --> 00:03:01,810
How have you been, Mr. Phurit?

49
00:03:03,070 --> 00:03:03,720
Longing.

50
00:03:04,870 --> 00:03:06,240
If Nawa had a choice,

51
00:03:06,780 --> 00:03:08,870
he'd still want to live his life with you.

52
00:03:09,570 --> 00:03:13,340
Thank you, Ping.
You made me realize something.

53
00:03:24,480 --> 00:03:24,980
Silp.

54
00:03:26,230 --> 00:03:26,760
Mr. Phurit.

55
00:03:28,220 --> 00:03:28,980
What's the matter?

56
00:03:29,650 --> 00:03:31,710
I believe it now that mermen really exist.

57
00:03:32,810 --> 00:03:34,160
Silp, could you tell me if you've ever

58
00:03:34,590 --> 00:03:35,810
met a mermaid before?

59
00:03:37,950 --> 00:03:38,930
Where did you see one?

60
00:03:40,540 --> 00:03:41,770
Please tell me.

61
00:03:43,010 --> 00:03:44,570
It's really important to my life.

62
00:03:46,810 --> 00:03:47,990
You know Phraphai, right?

63
00:03:49,260 --> 00:03:51,220
Do you know where his house is?

64
00:03:51,220 --> 00:03:52,830
The thing you're so distressed about…

65
00:03:54,010 --> 00:03:55,540
it's about that boy named Nawa, yes?

66
00:03:59,630 --> 00:04:01,580
What I fear the most is

67
00:04:02,850 --> 00:04:06,830
a deep relationship between
a human and a merman.

68
00:04:10,590 --> 00:04:13,060
Silp, you know that Nawa is...

69
00:04:16,300 --> 00:04:16,960
Please, sit down.

70
00:04:27,950 --> 00:04:30,390
That scale you once asked me about,

71
00:04:31,900 --> 00:04:34,410
it was the mermen scale of someone I loved.

72
00:04:37,630 --> 00:04:39,200
When I was about your age,

73
00:04:40,710 --> 00:04:42,270
I was someone with courage,

74
00:04:43,040 --> 00:04:45,240
dreams, and love.

75
00:04:47,720 --> 00:04:49,220
I fell in love with a merman,

76
00:04:50,170 --> 00:04:51,800
and I truly believed with all my heart

77
00:04:52,690 --> 00:04:54,250
that we could be together.

78
00:04:56,250 --> 00:04:57,580
Our difference in species

79
00:04:57,960 --> 00:04:59,740
didn't matter to me at all.

80
00:04:59,950 --> 00:05:01,950
(20 years ago)

81
00:05:01,950 --> 00:05:04,130
Silp, are you sure about meeting my parents?

82
00:05:05,150 --> 00:05:07,880
Yeah. They need to know that

83
00:05:08,160 --> 00:05:09,550
we love each other.

84
00:05:10,590 --> 00:05:13,680
I'll make your parents accept me.

85
00:05:17,330 --> 00:05:19,250
Whether merman or human,

86
00:05:20,010 --> 00:05:21,560
we all have the same heart.

87
00:05:22,770 --> 00:05:25,170
I believe your parents will understand.

88
00:05:26,420 --> 00:05:29,080
And after that, we'll open that café

89
00:05:29,290 --> 00:05:30,730
we dreamed about together.

90
00:05:37,120 --> 00:05:38,020
- Honey!
- Silp!

91
00:05:38,610 --> 00:05:40,080
A human and a merman can't love each other!

92
00:05:40,780 --> 00:05:41,750
You know full well

93
00:05:42,240 --> 00:05:44,080
humans are hunting our kind

94
00:05:45,170 --> 00:05:47,140
and you still insist on loving one of them?

95
00:05:48,700 --> 00:05:50,250
Both humans and mermen

96
00:05:50,810 --> 00:05:53,230
have good and bad people.

97
00:05:53,790 --> 00:05:54,940
I've never wanted to harm Vee,

98
00:05:55,070 --> 00:05:56,760
nor take advantage of him in any way.

99
00:05:57,510 --> 00:05:58,760
You're too naïve, boy.

100
00:05:59,840 --> 00:06:01,150
What you said proves

101
00:06:01,640 --> 00:06:03,180
you don't understand anything at all.

102
00:06:04,160 --> 00:06:06,480
This world isn't just the two of you!

103
00:06:07,400 --> 00:06:10,200
I love Vee. No matter what happens,
I won't stop loving him.

104
00:06:11,200 --> 00:06:13,350
And I'll protect him from everything.

105
00:06:15,650 --> 00:06:17,010
If you won't listen,

106
00:06:18,380 --> 00:06:20,110
then I'll kill you right here and now!

107
00:06:23,400 --> 00:06:25,290
- Dad, no!
- Honey, calm down!

108
00:06:25,870 --> 00:06:28,380
This? This is the person
who claims he'll protect my son?

109
00:06:29,550 --> 00:06:30,550
Pathetic.

110
00:06:32,500 --> 00:06:34,860
Silp, let's leave here.

111
00:06:38,000 --> 00:06:38,600
Vee!

112
00:06:42,840 --> 00:06:44,210
Go report this to the headman.

113
00:06:46,190 --> 00:06:47,410
Tell him to bring our son back.

114
00:06:52,800 --> 00:06:54,390
Are you still thinking about what Dad said?

115
00:06:57,740 --> 00:06:58,880
Don't worry about it.

116
00:06:59,790 --> 00:07:02,000
I know you can protect me.

117
00:07:03,390 --> 00:07:05,080
And I'll protect you too.

118
00:07:06,130 --> 00:07:08,380
We're a couple, we help each other.

119
00:07:09,590 --> 00:07:11,480
I can't let you be the only one
taking care of me.

120
00:07:14,220 --> 00:07:16,170
Thank you for staying by my side.

121
00:07:27,050 --> 00:07:28,140
What's this? What the hell?

122
00:07:28,140 --> 00:07:29,630
This the one you said is the merman?

123
00:07:29,630 --> 00:07:31,780
Yeah. That's him. No mistake.

124
00:07:33,950 --> 00:07:35,220
Vee! Run!

125
00:07:35,810 --> 00:07:36,520
Go!

126
00:07:37,200 --> 00:07:38,630
Hey! No! Don't!

127
00:07:41,860 --> 00:07:42,420
A monster

128
00:07:42,650 --> 00:07:44,450
like this doesn't deserve a human.

129
00:07:45,570 --> 00:07:46,010
Let's go!

130
00:07:53,700 --> 00:07:54,310
Vee.

131
00:07:56,350 --> 00:07:56,880
Vee!

132
00:07:59,390 --> 00:07:59,990
Vee!

133
00:08:00,880 --> 00:08:01,390
Vee!

134
00:08:02,430 --> 00:08:02,920
Vee!

135
00:08:04,340 --> 00:08:05,130
Stay with me!

136
00:08:05,770 --> 00:08:07,200
I'll take you to the hospital right now!

137
00:08:08,630 --> 00:08:10,990
I'm sorry! I'm so sorry!

138
00:08:11,890 --> 00:08:13,170
Why are you apologizing?

139
00:08:14,660 --> 00:08:16,090
You didn't do anything wrong.

140
00:08:17,260 --> 00:08:18,480
Don't blame yourself.

141
00:08:20,540 --> 00:08:21,550
You once said you

142
00:08:25,640 --> 00:08:27,040
liked me when I was in my merman form.

143
00:08:28,130 --> 00:08:30,570
I was saving it for the day we opened our café.

144
00:08:31,340 --> 00:08:35,740
But I guess I have to give it to you now instead…

145
00:08:37,890 --> 00:08:39,070
I love you so much, Silp.

146
00:08:42,770 --> 00:08:43,370
Vee!

147
00:08:44,590 --> 00:08:46,220
Vee! Stay with me.

148
00:08:46,880 --> 00:08:47,490
Vee!

149
00:08:48,820 --> 00:08:49,510
Vee!

150
00:08:51,000 --> 00:08:52,590
Vee! Stay with me!

151
00:08:53,340 --> 00:08:54,890
Vee! Talk to me! Vee!

152
00:08:55,640 --> 00:08:57,180
Vee, please stay with me!

153
00:08:58,060 --> 00:08:58,780
Vee!

154
00:09:07,310 --> 00:09:09,840
When humans and mermen
get involved with each other,

155
00:09:10,680 --> 00:09:14,030
it only leads to tragedies
that repeat endlessly.

156
00:09:15,640 --> 00:09:17,080
That's why I want you to let this go.

157
00:09:18,070 --> 00:09:20,210
I understand how hard it is…

158
00:09:21,050 --> 00:09:23,700
but it's what's best for you
and for that boy.

159
00:09:27,310 --> 00:09:28,760
You want me to just give up like this?

160
00:09:30,690 --> 00:09:31,850
After that incident,

161
00:09:32,510 --> 00:09:35,210
I tried to investigate the people
who killed my lover…

162
00:09:36,520 --> 00:09:38,200
and I found the truth.

163
00:09:40,220 --> 00:09:43,690
Everything Vee's father once said was true.

164
00:09:45,230 --> 00:09:47,730
This world isn't just about me and Vee.

165
00:09:48,970 --> 00:09:50,490
There are many people

166
00:09:51,170 --> 00:09:53,710
who refuse to let humans and mermen
love each other.

167
00:09:55,480 --> 00:09:57,470
And that is the real reason

168
00:09:58,020 --> 00:10:01,230
humans and mermen can never be together.

169
00:10:03,000 --> 00:10:04,170
What truth?

170
00:10:06,240 --> 00:10:07,420
20 years ago,

171
00:10:08,670 --> 00:10:11,180
there really was a group hunting mermen
on Khen island.

172
00:10:12,830 --> 00:10:14,820
And the one behind everything…

173
00:10:16,220 --> 00:10:18,880
was headman Chan, Phraphai's father.

174
00:10:23,240 --> 00:10:24,090
Why?

175
00:10:25,190 --> 00:10:26,360
Why would he do that?

176
00:10:27,580 --> 00:10:31,190
To show all mermen how disgusting
humans supposedly are.

177
00:10:32,420 --> 00:10:34,740
Then he played the hero,

178
00:10:35,560 --> 00:10:38,560
so they'd obey him unquestioningly.

179
00:10:39,530 --> 00:10:42,480
Especially his command to never get
involved with humans again.

180
00:10:44,070 --> 00:10:46,140
And I believe Phraphai

181
00:10:46,910 --> 00:10:48,860
thinks exactly the same way as his father.

182
00:10:50,250 --> 00:10:52,330
Then I have to bring Nawa back.

183
00:10:54,240 --> 00:10:56,100
If Nawa and I truly can't be together,

184
00:10:57,270 --> 00:10:59,930
then that decision should be ours

185
00:11:00,900 --> 00:11:02,150
not anyone else's.

186
00:11:02,520 --> 00:11:03,930
You really think this problem

187
00:11:03,930 --> 00:11:05,640
is that simple to fix?

188
00:11:08,350 --> 00:11:11,190
I know how big this is.

189
00:11:13,770 --> 00:11:15,450
But living while feeling like

190
00:11:16,240 --> 00:11:17,720
you're already dead…

191
00:11:18,950 --> 00:11:20,540
That's even worse.

192
00:11:26,690 --> 00:11:29,530
I know you understand

193
00:11:30,060 --> 00:11:31,130
how I feel.

194
00:11:36,150 --> 00:11:37,970
I have to bring Nawa back,

195
00:11:39,970 --> 00:11:41,540
even if it costs me my life.

196
00:11:47,860 --> 00:11:49,550
And I'll prove to you that

197
00:11:51,320 --> 00:11:53,080
love can happen between anyone,

198
00:11:54,500 --> 00:11:57,420
human, mermen,

199
00:11:59,150 --> 00:12:00,410
whatever.

200
00:12:03,560 --> 00:12:06,560
Love doesn't need conditions.

201
00:12:09,360 --> 00:12:10,050
You're right.

202
00:12:11,460 --> 00:12:12,830
What I couldn't do,

203
00:12:14,270 --> 00:12:15,650
maybe you can.

204
00:12:25,220 --> 00:12:27,920
Phraphai's home is in the mermen village.

205
00:12:30,230 --> 00:12:31,980
Take a boat west.

206
00:12:33,220 --> 00:12:35,790
Go far. You'll find it.

207
00:13:11,800 --> 00:13:12,780
Why the hell are you here?

208
00:13:13,930 --> 00:13:14,930
I know everything.

209
00:13:16,580 --> 00:13:17,710
